==English==
===Noun===
'''apple of discord'''

# Allegorically, an object which sows dissention and anger.  In Greek [[Mythology]] the [[goddess]] [[Eris]] (goddess of strife and discord) threw an apple made of gold with a inscription "for the fairest" (in the Greek it is explicit fairest female) on to the table for the wedding banquet of Thetis and Peleus, which the [[Olympian deities were attending]].  This sparked extreme argument leading to the judgment of Paris, which caused the Trojan war.